346
00:21:31,770 --> 00:21:34,240
好  我告诉你真相
All right. Here's the truth.

347
00:21:34,540 --> 00:21:39,990
我不再为他工作了  我不再为他烤排骨了
I don't work for him no more. I don't serve him ribs no more.

348
00:21:40,040 --> 00:21:42,660
我不想再跟他有任何关系
I don't want nothing to do with him no more.

349
00:21:42,660 --> 00:21:46,700
即使我恨他  我也的确恨他
Even if I hated him, and I do hate him...

350
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:51,670
我也不会告密  对警察  对记者
I don't snitch. Not to cops, not to reporters.

351
00:21:51,670 --> 00:21:53,060
对谁都不会
Not to anybody.

352
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:58,120
离我远点
Leave me the fuck alone.

353
00:22:05,120 --> 00:22:06,070
好了
Okay.

354
00:22:15,210 --> 00:22:18,620
林肯和罗斯福都是共和党的先进分子
Lincoln and Roosevelt were progressive Republicans.

355
00:22:20,570 --> 00:22:23,630
-杰弗逊是一名有远见的保守党  -是的
- Jefferson was a visionary Conservative. - Yeah!

356
00:22:23,630 --> 00:22:27,640
乔治·华盛顿是位强大的领袖
George Washington was a strong commander in chief.

357
00:22:28,370 --> 00:22:31,530
威廉·康威拥有所有这些品质
William Conway embodies all these qualities.

358
00:22:31,540 --> 00:22:35,010
我为背书他竞选总统而骄傲
I proudly endorse his candidacy for president,

359
00:22:35,240 --> 00:22:38,940
我也希望我们州的每个人都这么做
and I ask everyone in our great state to do the same.

360
00:22:38,950 --> 00:22:42,650
欢迎未来的美国总统  威廉·康威
The next President of the United States, William Conway!

361
00:22:56,140 --> 00:22:59,780
你们的支持让我受宠若惊
I'm... I'm humbled by your endorsement,

362
00:22:59,880 --> 00:23:03,610
我身后这些伟人遗留的贡献也让我自愧不如
and by the legacy of these great men behind me.

363
00:23:03,610 --> 00:23:06,830
接任他们是一项艰巨的任务
Now, they all left very big shoes to fill.

364
00:23:07,150 --> 00:23:10,200
知道谁完全没有接任的资格吗
You know who hasn't come even close to filling them?

365
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:12,650
弗兰克·安德伍德
Frank Underwood.

366
00:23:32,700 --> 00:23:33,920
我该离开
I should go.

367
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:36,990
我们降落之后
Once we land.

368
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,460
我就飞回东海岸
I'll get a flight back to the East Coast.

369
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:44,040
-汤姆...  -你不用多说了
- Tom... - You don't have to say anything.

370
00:24:14,630 --> 00:24:16,760
有人向房子扔鸡蛋
We've had eggs thrown at the house.

371
00:24:16,760 --> 00:24:20,190
番茄  牛粪  什么都有
Tomatoes, cow dung. You name it.

372
00:24:20,190 --> 00:24:22,880
南达科他州十分支持康威
South Dakota's big Conway country.

373
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:25,720
我们一生都住在这儿  也在这儿养育后代
We've been here all our lives. We raised our son here.

374
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:27,680
从未遇到过这种情况
It's just beyond our experience.

375
00:24:27,680 --> 00:24:29,400
这些人都是我们的邻居
All these folks are our neighbors.

376
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:31,870
可我一把标志竖起来
But once I put that sign up...

377
00:24:32,300 --> 00:24:35,820
康威州长是退伍军人  而且有孩子
Governor Conway is a veteran. He has children.

378
00:24:36,340 --> 00:24:37,840
为什么选我们  而不是他
Why us and not him?

379
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:42,290
当我们看到你们两个在党代会
When we saw you two at the convention...

380
00:24:42,910 --> 00:24:45,060
我说不清  看上去真像对儿好搭档
I don't know. It just seemed like a real partnership.

381
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:54,490
爱  深沉  坚定的爱
Love. Deep, unwavering love.

382
00:24:54,640 --> 00:24:57,330
感谢你们提醒我
I wanna thank you for reminding me

383
00:24:57,330 --> 00:24:59,650
那种爱有多重要
how important that kind of love is.

384
00:24:59,740 --> 00:25:02,510
它真的很重要  我们容易忙于竞选
Because it is. It's easy to get caught up in the campaign

385
00:25:02,510 --> 00:25:07,560
而忘记弗兰西斯和我是怎样走到这一步的
and to forget how Francis and I got here in the first place,

386
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:10,430
记得我们不仅是总统和第一夫人
to remember that we're not just President and First Lady,

387
00:25:10,430 --> 00:25:11,900
或丈夫和妻子
or husband and wife.

388
00:25:12,690 --> 00:25:13,860
我们是搭档
We're partners.

389
00:25:13,860 --> 00:25:18,110
我们决定要一起解决所有事
We have made a choice to tackle everything together.

390
00:25:20,090 --> 00:25:22,890
我们超越了美丽和完美
We go beyond what's pretty and perfect,

391
00:25:22,890 --> 00:25:26,680
超越了恐惧  困难和未知
beyond what's scary, difficult and unknown.

392
00:25:27,110 --> 00:25:29,920
我们不仅是候选人名单上的搭档
We're not just partners on the ticket.

393
00:25:30,530 --> 00:25:32,200
我们也是生活中的搭档
We're partners in life.

394
00:25:34,630 --> 00:25:35,420
总统先生
Mr. President.

395
00:25:35,420 --> 00:25:36,960
众议院情报委员会里
You have someone on the inside of

396
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:38,210
有人给你
the House Intelligence Committee

397
00:25:38,210 --> 00:25:40,740
提供机密信息
feeding you classified information.

398
00:25:40,750 --> 00:25:41,700
我是在任州长
I'm a sitting governor.

399
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:43,630
获得信息没什么错
There's nothing wrong with staying informed.

400
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:46,650
所有共和党人都在反对俄罗斯的介入
Every Republican is against the Russians being involved.

401
00:25:46,650 --> 00:25:49,170
